In [8]:
def summarize_cat(col_name):
    sorted_values = sorted(non_num_data[col_name].value_counts().iteritems(), key = lambda x:x[1], reverse=True)
    remaining_per = 100
    for (value, count) in sorted_values:
        per = count / len(non_num_data) * 100
        if per >= 1:
            print(f'{value} : {per:.2f}%')
        else :
            print(f'Others : {remaining_per:.2f}%')
            break
        remaining_per = remaining_per - per

In [19]:
def get_integer_mapping(le):
    '''
    Return a dict mapping labels to their integer values
    from an SKlearn LabelEncoder
    le = a fitted SKlearn LabelEncoder
    '''
    res = {}
    for cl in le.classes_:
        res.update({cl:le.transform([cl])[0]})

    return res

In [3]:
def get_measures_clf(y_pred,y_test):
    measures = {}
    measures["accuracy"]=accuracy_score(y_pred,y_test)
    measures["precision"]=precision_score(y_pred,y_test,average='weighted')
    measures["recall"]=recall_score(y_pred,y_test,average='weighted')
    measures["F1"]=f1_score(y_pred,y_test,average='weighted')
